description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an experienced band 4 Administrator to work in our rapidly expanding Perinatal Mental Health Team. The North London Partners Specialist Perinatal Mental Health Service is a community mental health service for pregnant and postnatal women with severe and complex mental illness. The aim of the team is to detect, prevent and treat perinatal mental health problems to improve the experience of pregnancy and the first year postpartum for women and their families.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a proactive and motivated individual to join our team of administrators in providing exceptional administrative support for a 1 year fixed term period. This is an exciting opportunity to join the North London Partners Specialist Perinatal Mental Health Service with the opportunity to work across sites and gain experience in a varied, dynamic and multi-disciplinary team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidates will have proven administrative skills and the ability to work at pace and use their own initiative. You will also bring experience of customer/patient care in order to help improve the care and experience of patients seen within the service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This job will be based at Forest Road Health Centre, N9 7HD but you will be expected to cover administrators at other sites.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;_____________________________________________________________________________________________________&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;N.B. This vacancy may close early due to high number of applications&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
